    {
      "id": "3dee08a986e343ee552cc16bd4b43d74a027a45c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-11-21 14:39:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: (1 inline comment)\n\nOriginally, we only support single MDS, means only one quota slave on MDT, so there was no adjust qunit mechanism for inode quota. But in your patch, you began to consider DNE case. So qunit adjust mechanism for inode quota should be considered also. Although it is not related with your patch, it is better to implement that in the future, sooner or later.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "f9c574c4fcaab381cfb85fa589826d1118591f1c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 7,
        "name": "Johann Lombardi",
        "email": "johann.lombardi@intel.com",
        "username": "johann",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-11-21 15:43:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nqunit adjustment is actually only needed between master & slaves (qunit adjustment is even removed from LOV/OSC on Orion since those layers are replaced by LOD/OSP on the MDS) and LMV won't be used for MDS communications in DNE (it will use LOD/OSP instead).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
